---
description: Dotfiles repo conventions for stow and AI config placement
alwaysApply: true
---

This is a macOS dotfiles repo managed with GNU Stow. Every top-level directory (without a leading dot) is a stow package that mirrors the structure of `~`.

**When creating new files, decide scope first:**

- Global (every machine) → put inside a stow package matching the target path under `~`
- Repo-local Cursor config → `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` at the repo root (never stowed)
- Generated/local output → add to both `.gitignore` and `.stowrc`

**AI config packages:**

- `ai/` → `~/.claude/` (Claude config, skills, MCP servers), `~/AGENTS.md` (Claude + agents), and `~/.cursor/rules/agents.mdc` (Cursor global rules)
- `graphify-out/` is gitignored and excluded from stow — do not commit it
